    "summary": "My perspective as a designer is that at this moment timing is perfect to rediscover products and processes which are already existing. We should find ways on how to use these in the most optimal, sustainable way. With my projects I'm mostly researching existing production systems, and looking for ways on how to create innovative plans which companies can implement to make their product or process more durable. Waste is a great raw material, we just have to give it new value, and a new destination.\n\nSocial Design is another thing that keeps me busy. Using storytelling and human interaction to start a conversation, and create new insights makes me very much an encourager of doing field research in order to understand my projects, subjects and users.",
